Syrian President Bashar Assad condemned the assassination as "a horrible criminal action" and offered his country's condolences and support to Hariri's family and Lebanon at large.
Opposition leaders on Monday held Lebanese and Syrian governments responsible for the assassination of former Prime Minister Rafik Hariri, demanded Syrian troops withdraw from Lebanon within the next three months and called on the international community to intervene to help "this captive nation."
It also called for a three-day strike and demanded an international commission to investigate the assassination "in light of the lack of confidence of the Lebanese in this government."
